The paper deals with the design of low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes and their iterative message-passing decoding, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT). The proposed method involves the use of spatially coupled LDPC codes (SC-LDPCCs), which are often used in network coding and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of quasi-cyclic (QC) LDPC codes, which are a type of structured code often used in coding theory and cryptography (cs.SI). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves a search space and a greedy approach, which are common techniques in optimization and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method through numerical simulations, which is a common approach in computer networks and communication (cs.CC).
